ABC Sports begins its fourth season of NHL coverage
this Saturday, Jan. 11, with three regional broadcasts
at 1 p.m. ET. Brett Hull and the Red Wings face
Eastern Conference powerhouse Philadelphia; Mike
Modano and the Dallas Stars host their Western
Conference rivals, the Colorado Avalanche; and Eric
Lindros and the New York Rangers face off against
Mario Lemieux and the Pittsburgh Penguins.

Saturday's broadcast also includes the announcement
of the starting lineups for the 53rd NHL All-Star Game
presented by Nextel. Don't miss it!

http://nl4@nhl.com/onthefly/schedules/abc_sked.html



JANUARY'S IMPACT! NHL.COM'S ONLINE MAGAZINE
The latest issue of Impact! -- NHL.com's online
magazine -- is devoted to the men who wear the
captain's "C". Find out why being an NHL captain
is an honor, but also brings lots of hard work and
responsibility. It is a role that Mark Messier
has embraced throughout his lengthy career.

http://nl4@nhl.com/intheslot/read/impact/index.html



