53RD NHL ALL-STAR GAME PRESENTED BY NEXTEL
The 53rd NHL All-Star Game, presented by Nextel,
takes place Sunday, Feb. 2, 2003 at the Office
Depot Center in Sunrise, Fla., and will be
televised by ABC Sports in the U.S. and CBC and
RDS in Canada. Fan balloting is complete and
the coaches and starting lineups will be
announced this week. Check out NHL.com's full
All-Star section for all the details on this
year's game!

http://nl4@nhl.com/allstar2003/index.html



EASTERN CONFERENCE NOTEBOOK: ISLES ISSUE CHALLENGE
In his weekly Eastern Conference Notebook for
NHL.com, Chuck Gormley says the New York Islanders
are alive and breathing again after a rough start
and have issued a challenge to the Flyers, Devils
and Penguins. Gormley runs down the Eastern
Conference every Tuesday and Doug Ward covers the
West each Thursday, only on NHL.com!

http://nl4@nhl.com/intheslot/read/east/index.html


